      "hadith_number": "2621",
      "english_translation": "Narrated by Jabir ibn Atik al-Ansari: Abdullah ibn Umar came to us among Banu Mu'awiyah and said: Do you know what are the three things for which the Messenger of Allah ﷺ supplicated? I said: Yes. He said: Inform me of them. I said: He supplicated that no enemy besides them should overcome them, and that they should not be destroyed by famine, and he granted these two. And he supplicated that internal strife should not be placed among them, and this was denied. Then he said: You are correct. Strife will continue until the Day of Judgment.",
